{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":634,"text":"How often do we hear\nthat people just don't care?"},{"time":4958,"text":"How many times have you been told"},{"time":6573,"text":"that real, substantial change\nisn't possible"},{"time":9838,"text":"because most people are too selfish,"},{"time":11937,"text":"too stupid or too lazy"},{"time":13893,"text":"to try to make a difference\nin their community?"},{"time":16549,"text":"I propose to you today\nthat apathy as we think we know it"},{"time":19667,"text":"doesn't actually exist;"},{"time":21402,"text":"but rather, that people do care,"},{"time":23600,"text":"but that we live in a world\nthat actively discourages engagement"},{"time":27333,"text":"by constantly putting obstacles\nand barriers in our way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30718,"text":"I'll give you some\nexamples of what I mean."},{"time":32774,"text":"Let's start with city hall."},{"time":34863,"text":"You ever see one of these before?"},{"time":36958,"text":"This is a newspaper ad."},{"time":38600,"text":"It's a notice of a zoning application\nchange for a new office building"},{"time":41992,"text":"so the neighborhood\nknows what's happening."},{"time":44087,"text":"As you can see, it's impossible to read."},{"time":46033,"text":"You need to get halfway down"},{"time":47433,"text":"to even find out which address\nthey're talking about,"},{"time":49991,"text":"and then further down,\nin tiny 10-point font,"},{"time":52159,"text":"to find out how to actually get involved."},{"time":54219,"text":"Imagine if the private sector\nadvertised in the same way --"},{"time":57370,"text":"if Nike wanted to sell a pair of shoes --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59436,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60600,"text":"And put an ad in the paper like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62589,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66600,"text":"Now, that would never happen."},{"time":69435,"text":"You'll never see an ad like that,"},{"time":71038,"text":"because Nike actually wants\nyou to buy their shoes,"},{"time":73493,"text":"whereas the city of Toronto\nclearly doesn't want you involved"},{"time":76398,"text":"with the planning process,"},{"time":77674,"text":"otherwise their ads would look\nsomething like this,"},{"time":80114,"text":"with all the information laid out clearly."},{"time":82155,"text":"As long as the city's putting out\nnotices like this"},{"time":84596,"text":"to try to get people engaged,"},{"time":86046,"text":"then of course people\naren't going to be engaged."},{"time":88404,"text":"But that's not apathy;\nthat's intentional exclusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92324,"text":"Public space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93612,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96521,"text":"The manner in which we mistreat\nour public spaces"},{"time":98880,"text":"is a huge obstacle towards any type\nof progressive political change,"},{"time":103164,"text":"because we've essentially put a price tag\non freedom of expression."},{"time":106387,"text":"Whoever has the most money\ngets the loudest voice,"},{"time":108996,"text":"dominating the visual\nand mental environment."},{"time":111419,"text":"The problem with this model\nis there are some amazing messages"},{"time":114423,"text":"that need to be said,\nthat aren't profitable to say."},{"time":117288,"text":"So you're never going\nto see them on a billboard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120755,"text":"The media plays an important role"},{"time":122392,"text":"in developing our relationship\nwith political change,"},{"time":125600,"text":"mainly by ignoring politics and focusing\non celebrities and scandals,"},{"time":129775,"text":"but even when they do talk\nabout important political issues,"},{"time":132652,"text":"they do it in a way that I feel\ndiscourages engagement."},{"time":135529,"text":"I'll give you an example."},{"time":136771,"text":"The \"Now\" magazine from last week:\nprogressive, downtown weekly in Toronto."},{"time":140388,"text":"This is the cover story."},{"time":141600,"text":"It's an article\nabout a theater performance,"},{"time":144112,"text":"and it starts with basic\ninformation about where it is,"},{"time":146894,"text":"in case you actually want to go and see\nit after you've read the article --"},{"time":150443,"text":"where, the time, the website."},{"time":152250,"text":"Same with this -- it's a movie review."},{"time":154679,"text":"An art review."},{"time":156287,"text":"A book review -- where the reading\nis in case you want to go."},{"time":159449,"text":"A restaurant -- you might not\nwant to just read about it,"},{"time":162183,"text":"maybe you want to go there."},{"time":163634,"text":"So they tell you where it is, the prices,\nthe address, the phone number, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167431,"text":"Then you get to their political articles."},{"time":169432,"text":"Here's a great article about an important\nelection race that's happening."},{"time":172916,"text":"It talks about the candidates,\nwritten very well,"},{"time":175269,"text":"but no information, no follow-up,\nno websites for the campaigns,"},{"time":178520,"text":"no information about when the debates\nare, where the campaign offices are."},{"time":182069,"text":"Here's another good article,"},{"time":183522,"text":"about a new campaign\nopposing privatization of transit,"},{"time":186600,"text":"without any contact information\nfor the campaign."},{"time":189338,"text":"The message seems to be"},{"time":190886,"text":"that the readers are most likely\nto want to eat, maybe read a book,"},{"time":194321,"text":"maybe see a movie, but not be engaged\nin their community."},{"time":197108,"text":"You might think this is a small thing,\nbut I think it's important,"},{"time":200270,"text":"because it sets a tone"},{"time":201690,"text":"and it reinforces the dangerous idea\nthat politics is a spectator sport."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208163,"text":"Heroes: How do we view leadership?"},{"time":210432,"text":"Look at these 10 movies.\nWhat do they have in common?"},{"time":213119,"text":"Anyone?"},{"time":216038,"text":"They all have heroes who were chosen."},{"time":218136,"text":"Someone came up to them and said,\n\"You're the chosen one."},{"time":220875,"text":"There's a prophecy.\nYou have to save the world.\""},{"time":223173,"text":"And then they go off and save the world\nbecause they've been told to,"},{"time":226499,"text":"with a few people tagging along."},{"time":228082,"text":"This helps me understand"},{"time":229262,"text":"why a lot of people have trouble\nseeing themselves as leaders --"},{"time":232313,"text":"because it sends all the wrong messages\nabout what leadership is about."},{"time":235861,"text":"A heroic effort is a collective effort,"},{"time":238398,"text":"number one."},{"time":239928,"text":"Number two, it's imperfect;\nit's not very glamorous,"},{"time":243320,"text":"and doesn't suddenly start\nand suddenly end."},{"time":245526,"text":"It's an ongoing process your whole life."},{"time":247612,"text":"But most importantly, it's voluntary."},{"time":249413,"text":"It's voluntary."},{"time":250855,"text":"As long as we're teaching our kids"},{"time":253242,"text":"that heroism starts when someone\nscratches a mark on your forehead,"},{"time":256688,"text":"or someone tells you\nyou're part of a prophecy,"},{"time":258938,"text":"they're missing the most important\ncharacteristic of leadership,"},{"time":261991,"text":"which is that it comes from within."},{"time":263702,"text":"It's about following\nyour own dreams, uninvited,"},{"time":267600,"text":"and then working with others\nto make those dreams come true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270600,"text":"Political parties: oh, boy."},{"time":272999,"text":"Political parties could and should be\none of the basic entry points"},{"time":277516,"text":"for people to get engaged in politics."},{"time":279467,"text":"Instead, they've become, sadly,"},{"time":281756,"text":"uninspiring and uncreative organizations"},{"time":284666,"text":"that rely so heavily on market research\nand polling and focus groups"},{"time":288600,"text":"that they end up all saying\nthe same thing,"},{"time":290672,"text":"pretty much regurgitating back\nto us what we already want to hear"},{"time":293792,"text":"at the expense of putting forward\nbold and creative ideas."},{"time":296600,"text":"And people can smell that,\nand it feeds cynicism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299380,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305724,"text":"Charitable status."},{"time":307192,"text":"Groups who have charitable status\nin Canada aren't allowed to do advocacy."},{"time":310970,"text":"This is a huge problem\nand a huge obstacle to change,"},{"time":313525,"text":"because it means that some\nof the most passionate and informed voices"},{"time":317021,"text":"are completely silenced,\nespecially during election time."},{"time":319928,"text":"Which leads us to the last one,\nwhich is: our elections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323696,"text":"As you may have noticed,"},{"time":324888,"text":"our elections in Canada\nare a complete joke."},{"time":327019,"text":"We use out-of-date systems"},{"time":328534,"text":"that are unfair and create random results."},{"time":330859,"text":"Canada's currently led by a party"},{"time":332600,"text":"that most Canadians didn't actually want."},{"time":335072,"text":"How can we honestly and genuinely\nencourage more people to vote"},{"time":338711,"text":"when votes don't count in Canada?"},{"time":341012,"text":"You add all this up together,\nand of course people are apathetic."},{"time":344404,"text":"It's like trying to run into a brick wall."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346488,"text":"Now, I'm not trying to be negative\nby throwing all these obstacles out"},{"time":349829,"text":"and explaining what's in our way."},{"time":351453,"text":"Quite the opposite --"},{"time":352630,"text":"I actually think people are amazing\nand smart and that they do care,"},{"time":357217,"text":"but that, as I said,\nwe live in this environment"},{"time":359600,"text":"where all these obstacles\nare being put in our way."},{"time":363488,"text":"As long as we believe\nthat people, our own neighbors,"},{"time":366963,"text":"are selfish, stupid or lazy,"},{"time":370417,"text":"then there's no hope."},{"time":372804,"text":"But we can change\nall those things I mentioned."},{"time":375139,"text":"We can open up city hall."},{"time":376600,"text":"We can reform our electoral systems."},{"time":378356,"text":"We can democratize our public spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380357,"text":"My main message is:"},{"time":382153,"text":"if we can redefine apathy,"},{"time":383855,"text":"not as some kind of internal syndrome,"},{"time":385901,"text":"but as a complex web of cultural barriers\nthat reinforces disengagement,"},{"time":391329,"text":"and if we can clearly define,\nclearly identify what those obstacles are,"},{"time":396916,"text":"and then if we can work together\ncollectively to dismantle those obstacles,"},{"time":400531,"text":"then anything is possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401809,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402993,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}